731213f-a.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal events - Funeral procession: U. S. Grant.
731213f-a.text:
Parades, Celebrations and Municipal Events1 A southward view
on Broadway from a point to the north of Prince Street and across
same, showing what the writer believes to be the funeral procession
of Gen. U.S. Grant, marching northward to the temporary tomb in
Riverside Park. Leading to this conclusion is the fact that Auguust,
Bernheim, Bauer a Co. occupied No. 516 Broadway between 1882 and
1886 and subsequently became Bernheim, Bauer S Co. in 1888, occupy-
ing cquarters at 507-9-ll Broadway (opposite side of this thorough-
fare).
An account of this funeral appears in Harpers Magazine of
w2ctober 1885 (Vol. LNxI) on page 806; and the Independent of August
6, 1885 (Vo1. 37) on page 15.
Aummst 8, 1885.
